# Re-ported against LMCache v0.5.1.
# l1_manager.py: 3-way merge (context drift).  gds_context.py: adds Prometheus
# gauges for the NVMe<->GPU DMA byte counters (read/written).
#
# Note: earlier revisions of this patch also called ca._ensure_driver_open()
# in _open_and_register_slab() before ca.register_handle().  Dropped on v0.5.1 --
# upstream's register_handle()/register_buffer()/register_stream() now call
# _ensure_driver_open() internally as their first action, and the _gds_async
# dispatch shim re-exports only the public surface (register_* / close_driver),
# not the private _ensure_driver_open helper -- so the external call both was
# redundant and raised AttributeError on the shim.
#
